Description: March 1962. Crucifixion Spink. Certain features derived from Bruegel's Way to Calvary of 1564. In Mary's group on left the woman in despair is wether 'Mary Magdalen' from the Bruegel of 1564 also the peddlar with the basket. The ground [onleesbaar] quite different from B. Outlined in brown lines: architecture and figures on right. Man under cross in green - white stupid Lovers seen from back. Red staffage in centre. Distribution of red spots similar to Vienna Calvary. Line pale green with hightened with lighter green in bushes on right. Horsemen under cross seen from back cf. Conversion of St. Paul. Figures seen from back in background painted broadly and almost monochrome like Dutch XVII. P. Baltens or M. van Cleve? [...][scan]
